## Public Member Functions

### getEncodedPointer() {#ab0ceb7476c6b212e0f515e2a4cc9e551}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::optional&lt; uint64&#95;t &gt; DWARFDataExtractor::getEncodedPointer (uint64&#95;t &#42; Offset, uint8&#95;t Encoding, uint64&#95;t AbsPosOffset=0) const</>}>
Extracts a DWARF-encoded pointer in <code>Offset</code> using <code>Encoding</code>.

There is a DWARF encoding that uses a PC-relative adjustment. For these values, <code>AbsPosOffset</code> is used to fix them, which should reflect the absolute address of this pointer.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/dwarf/dwarfdataextractor-h/#l00084">84</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/dwarf/dwarfdataextractor-h">DWARFDataExtractor.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/dwarf/dwarfdataextractor-cpp/#l00072">72</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/dwarf/dwarfdataextractor-cpp">DWARFDataExtractor.cpp</a>.

### getInitialLength() {#a10e13073556511543a885ea96b61ff6c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::pair&lt; uint64&#95;t, dwarf::DwarfFormat &gt; DWARFDataExtractor::getInitialLength (uint64&#95;t &#42; Off, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> &#42; Err=nullptr) const</>}>
Extracts the DWARF &quot;initial length&quot; field, which can either be a 32-bit value smaller than 0xfffffff0, or the value 0xffffffff followed by a 64-bit length.

Returns the actual length, and the DWARF format which is encoded in the field. In case of errors, it returns &#123;0, DWARF32&#125; and leaves the offset unchanged.
